<p>A <b>time zone</b> is a region of the <a href="/wiki/Earth" title="Earth">earth</a> that has uniform <a href="/wiki/Standard_time" title="Standard time">standard time</a>, usually referred to as the <b>local time</b>. By convention, time zones compute their local time as an offset from <a href="/wiki/Coordinated_Universal_Time" title="Coordinated Universal Time">UTC</a> (see also <a href="/wiki/Greenwich_Mean_Time" title="Greenwich Mean Time">Greenwich Mean Time</a>). Local time is UTC plus the current time zone offset for the considered location.</p>
